# coverage.thresholds — per-package minimum statement coverage (percent).
#
# Format:  <import-path> <min-pct>     (per-package override)
#          default <min-pct>            (floor for any gated package not listed)
#          # comment / blank lines ignored
#
# Gate lives in scripts/coverage.sh (`make cover`). Packages matching the
# exclusion regex there (cmd/*, telemetry, connectorpb, pgtest/oidctest/
# sdktest, e2e) are measured but never gated — no entry needed.
#
# RATCHET: floors only ever rise. After raising coverage, run `make cover-bump`
# to rewrite this file to achieved-minus-epsilon, then commit.
#
# NOTE: seeded during M7 Workstream A with a permissive default so the gate can
# land green; Workstream B raises the weak packages, then `make cover-bump`
# tightens these floors. See docs/adr/0022-testing-and-benchmark-policy.md.



